Cell.Text: [S] S|I remember you, you were at Helgen. Speak to Legate Rikke. I suspect we could use someone like you.
S|[E] Are my men now giving free reign to anyone who wanders into the castle? | Do you have some reason to be here, citizen?
There something I can do for you? Perhaps direct you to the nearest prison...
Have we? | Oh. Of course. | You were at Helgen!
One of the prisoners, if I recall correctly.
Right... Helgen..
[S] G|I suspect we might have use for someone resourceful like you. Not many survived Helgen. | Besides, I'm sure your being imprisoned was all a terrible misunderstanding.
Hadvar's alive? I hope that's true. He's a damn good soldier. | But he hasn't reported in yet, so he can't exactly confirm your story. | In the meantime, why don't you have a chat with Legate Rikke.

Node.Caption: CW00TulliusGreetHadvar: I helped Hadvar escape. He said he'd vouch for me.

Cell.Text: I suppose that's true. Fine. | Why don't you have a chat with Legate Rikke?

Node.Caption: CW00TulliusGreetFreeToGo: I was set free. I could've gone anywhere. I came here to fight for the Empire.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Are you lost?

S|You survived Helgen? General Tullius told me what happened. Not many made it out alive... | [E] I've got a good feeling about you. And I don't often get good feelings about anything. A warrior knows to trust her gut... | I'm not going to go through the normal process with you. I've got a little test lined up. Pass that, and we'll talk about you joining the Legion.
About that test...
Are you ready to test yourself at Fort Hraagstad?
[S] Is that confidence, or bravado? Confidence I can use. Bravado gets soldiers killed. | We'll soon find out.

Node.Caption: CW00RikkeGreetHandleAnything: I can handle anything you throw at me.

Cell.Text: [E] I'm sending you to clear out Fort Hraagstad. If you survive, you'll pass. | If you die, then I'll have no further use for your corpse.
[E] The kind that evaluates your usefulness during... duress.

[E] The ancients built many of the fortresses that dot the landscape of Skyrim. | Sadly, most have fallen into disrepair. And nearly all have been overrun with bandits or other vagabonds. | Fort Hraagstad is one of the few that remains mostly intact. | [E] We're going to install a garrison there, but first, your going to clean out the bandits that have moved in.
G|Is that so? I was right about you.
S|Oh, not so confident now, are we?
Yes. This is a test. I don't think you're regular militia material. I want to see what you're capable of.
[S] G|Well, if you change your mind, you know what to do.
[S] G|Good. That's what I want to hear. Now go make it happen, soldier.
G|Good.
G|I see. Then there's nothing further to discuss. If you change you're mind, speak with the Legate.
